<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> be dead nuts on something • be dead set on something</xh5><p> <i>be dead nuts on something—</i>1. <i>(coll.)</i> placed precisely on the surface of smth.: He caught me <u>dead nuts on</u> the chin, Pepe thought as he lay on the ground. 2. <i>(coll.)</i> exactly correspond to smth.: The styling of the new convertible <u>is dead nuts on</u> what a car in this class should be: bold and aristocratic. 3. <i>(sl.)</i> be very fond of smth.; be delighted with smth.: Quite frankly, I wasn’t <u>dead nuts on</u> meeting with them.</p><p> <i>be dead set on something—</i>be fixed in one’s purpose; be determined on doing smth.: The administration <u>is dead set on</u> trying to destroy unions. <i>Cf.: make a dead set at something</i>—make a determined effort to gain smth.: People can’t be allowed to <u>make a dead set at</u> a property like this.</p> </entry>
